page.title: 03Holt Heath Nature Reserve
page.content: There are 3 types of snake Smooth Snake,Adder & Grass Snake.You are able to see the snakes and lizards at about 8.30 a.m. There are some badger setts on the site two on the N.side near Bull Barrow.The site is also home to a very big rabbit population with warrens on many parts particularly S.facing slopes. Although there are NOT any Dartford Warblers at present there are many species of birds to be found including some birds of prey,amongst the most regularly seen are the Hobby Kestrel and the occassional Harrier Of the plants the wetland species are the rarest these include,Bog Orchid,Bottle Orchid,Sundew,Marsh Gentian & Dorset Crossed-leaved Heather.Common Heather & Gorse are the plants commonly seen.
